import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['open'] = pd.to_numeric(data['open'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='open', kde=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of daily opening prices?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Opening Prices')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    ax = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='close', data=data)
    ax.set(xlabel='Date', ylabel='Closing Price')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the trend of daily closing prices over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
